=White Horse Monastery 白馬寺=
Buddhist temple in Luoyang, founded probably around 2nd cent. AD, first of its kind in China according to the legend of the dream of emperor Ming of the Later Han (r. 57-75). Palumbo (2005) points out that there were temples in many different cities in China with that name.

==Literature==
===Articles===
* Antonello Palumbo: Dharmaraksa and Kanthaka. White Horse Monasteries in Early Medieval China. In Silvio Vita and Giovanni Verardi: Buddhist Asia 1. Kyoto: Italian School of East Asian Studies, 2005: 167-216